Most adults spend the bulk of their waking hours at work. Why not leverage that time to improve their health and well-being? In this course, instructor Laura Putnam covers the business case for well-being and the critical role that managers play in empowering employees to engage with their well-being. Laura points out that wellness increases team performance and explains how you, as a manager, hold a unique role in persuading your team to engage with wellness. She shows you how to monitor your own well-being and your teamâ€™s. Laura also provides a template for every manager to create a positive multiplier effect for their team members.